  "prompt": "How to add a link in a Quora answer to another Quora answer when using Quora iPhone app?",
  "response": "To add a link to another Quora answer when using the Quora iPhone app, follow these steps:\n\n1. While writing your answer, tap the link/chain icon in the formatting toolbar (usually located near the bottom of the text input area).\n\n2. If the Quora answer you want to link is from the same browser or app session, you can:\n   - Copy the answer's URL\n   - Paste it into the link field\n   - Tap \"Add link\"\n\n3. Alternatively, you can:\n   - Go to the answer you want to link\n   - Tap the \"Share\" button\n   - Copy the link\n   - Return to your draft answer\n   - Paste the link\n\n4. If copying the full URL is difficult, you can also type the link text and tap the link icon to paste the URL.\n\nNote: Make sure the link is a full, valid Quora answer URL for it to work correctly.\n\nIf you're having trouble, you might want to draft the answer on a computer or use the mobile web version of Quora, which sometimes offers more formatting options.",
